OL,3,CHow can 'fart chambers' help fight
OL,4,Cglobal warming?
OL,6,FWhile methane remains in the
OL,7,Fatmosphere for only about ten to 12
OL,8,Fyears (compared to centuries for
OL,9,Fcarbon dioxide), its warming effect is
OL,10,Faround 28 times stronger.
OL,12,FSo, how can we measure these
OL,13,Femissions, and ultimately reduce them?
OL,15,FThe Game and Wildlife Conservation
OL,16,FTrust is trialling one unusual
OL,17,Fsolution: portable emissions chambers
OL,18,F(PACs) - nicknamed "fart chambers."
